# Notion Integration
# To enable Notion integration for lead capture:
# 1. Go to https://www.notion.so/my-integrations
# 2. Create a new integration named "AI Readiness Scorecard"
# 3. Copy the "Internal Integration Token" (starts with secret_...)
# 4. Share your Notion database with this integration
# 5. Add the token below (remove .example from filename)

VITE_NOTION_TOKEN=secret_your_notion_integration_token_here

# Notion Database ID (already configured)
# Database ID: e6af817ea8c040a49793df0a513311a6
# This is the database where all leads will be captured

# Database Schema Required:
# - Name (Title) - Primary field
# - Email (Email) - Contact email
# - Company (Rich Text) - Company name
# - Job Title (Rich Text) - User's role
# - Turnover (Select) - Options: "<1M", "1M-10M", "10M-50M", "50M+"
# - Lead Source (Select) - Options: "AI Readiness Scorecard", "Lead Magnet", "Survey", "Lead Response Crisis Form"
# - UTM Source (Rich Text) - Marketing attribution
# - UTM Medium (Rich Text) - Marketing attribution
# - UTM Campaign (Rich Text) - Marketing attribution
# - Timestamp (Date) - When form was submitted
# - Score (Number) - Overall readiness score (0-100), populated after quiz
# - Risk Level (Select) - Options: "High Risk", "At Risk", "Building Capability", "Ready", "Strong"
# - Weakest Dimension (Rich Text) - Which of 6 dimensions needs most work
# - Segment (Select) - Options: "Unsure", "Exploring", "Experimenting", "Piloting", "Scaling", "Embedded"
# - Status (Select) - Options: "New Lead", "Quiz Started", "Quiz Completed", "Contacted", "Qualified", "Unqualified"

# NOTE: If VITE_NOTION_TOKEN is not set, the app will work normally but won't save leads to Notion.
# The GoHighLevel (GHL) webhook will still function independently.
